caption.text: Had nothing to do, we decided to go to a place which is highly potential in its marine resource and almost all of the local people here work as fisher and they shelter in the same place that name is Kampung Baru Tengah. (1/5)

data.text: bihh masa ak bego btul vittt wkwkwkwk @evitasujianto

caption.text: As we were walking in the village, we saw some fishers that had finished their daily activity on the sea and we started to talk to them about what they do currently.While they were explaining about what they do, we jumped onto their fishing boat to see something that have a typical smell. Then after a lot of explaination, we conceived that some fishers will preserve their own caught fish directly by exposing it underneath the direct sunlight. The preservation is to keep the fish fresh and to make a typical saltiness by adding some salt. (2/5)

caption.text: After that, we walked to the harbour and met many children who told my friend to take a photo. (3/5)

We looked around the harbour and my friend found a spot for some photos between the harbour and the strange house. He tried to stand on the wood beam but it's very hard to stand on an old wood beam. So i took a photo of my friend on two wood beams because he was afraid to fall into seawater that contains all of the local's waste. (4/5)
Our simple trip took us into a beautiful scene that can't be held without a pleasure toward environment. (5/5)
